        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Configurable most-used provider metric and provider filter",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nMakes the \"Show most-used provider\" menu-bar feature configurable: which enabled providers are eligible, and how \"most-used\" is ranked. Previously the merged icon always auto-selected the provider closest to its rate limit, with no way to influence the choice.\r\n\r\nSurfaced as an inline sentence in Preferences → Display: *Show most-used provider **from** [providers ▾] **by** [metric ▾]*.\r\n\r\nAddresses #1777 and #1743.\r\n\r\nAppearance in settings:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"475\" height=\"33\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/ee92ce72-7098-4bf4-9c68-aab7113039df\" />\r\n\r\n<img width=\"477\" height=\"125\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/9cf98334-33ef-46c7-970e-b112f7b672e4\" />\r\n\r\n<img width=\"484\" height=\"84\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/64dcd4b4-a4ed-4c2a-b4ed-da728258f22a\" />\r\n\r\n## Ranking metric (#1777)\r\n\r\n`closest to rate limit` (default, unchanged behavior), `tokens used`, `dollars used` — the token/dollar metrics use current-session values from `CostUsageTokenSnapshot`; providers without a snapshot are skipped.\r\n\r\n## Candidate filter (#1743)\r\n\r\nA multi-select of the enabled providers eligible as \"most-used.\" Persists, reconciles when providers are enabled/disabled, and always keeps at least one selected.\r\n\r\nTo avoid inaccuracy from day-to-day conversation rate fluctuations, dollar comparisons are unavailable for providers without a dollar-per-token value stored.\r\n\r\n**Scope note:** this is an opt-in filter, not a default change — out of the box all enabled providers remain candidates, so the original case (Antigravity auto-showing despite being hidden in Overview) is resolved by deselecting it here. Happy to instead default the candidate set to the Overview selection if that's preferred. Affects only the collapsed menu-bar icon; the dropdown's last-viewed tab is unchanged.\r\n\r\n## Localization\r\n\r\nNew keys added to `en` and the `ar`/`fa`/`th` catalogs (which have strict key-parity tests); other locales fall back to English (parity tests relaxed for these specific keys).\r\n\r\n## Tests\r\n\r\nRanking per metric, tie ordering by enabled-provider order, nil-on-missing-snapshot, disabled-provider exclusion, candidate default/custom-subset persistence and reconcile, metric round-trip, and preview-label states. `swift build` is clean and the affected suites pass.\r\n",
